CAFE  number.  They  looked  at  some  of  the  drawbacks  to  the  pro-
gram. It certainly was successful. 

Senator KERRY. Do you know what they said, Ms. Administrator? 
You  know  what  they—sorry  to  interrupt  you—but  in  2001—that’s 
6 years ago now—they found that existing engine technologies were 
inexpensive  enough  to  pay  for  themselves  over  the  life  of  the  vehi-
cle,  and  could  enhance  fuel  economy  by  8  to  11  miles  per  gallon, 
with  no  net  consumer  cost.  And  with  most  fuel  economy  improve-
ments  for  SUVs  and  other  heavier  vehicles,  34  percent  increase 
from  18  to  28.  That’s  what  they  found  in  2001  technology.  Here 
